OK, so let's look at this.

00:30:51.100 --> 00:30:53.970
So you have sigma_2 here.

00:30:53.970 --> 00:30:55.345
Sigma_1 is 0.

00:30:57.970 --> 00:31:03.070
And you have R_1 equal to R_2.

00:31:03.070 --> 00:31:04.728
What is all R of P?

00:31:07.540 --> 00:31:08.380
It's R, right?

00:31:11.250 --> 00:31:13.300
Because the weighting
doesn't matter.

00:31:13.300 --> 00:31:18.170
So you know it's going
to fall along this line.

00:31:18.170 --> 00:31:22.710
So here is when
