00:31:31.170 --> 00:31:34.120
So you have a possible
combination along this line,

00:31:34.120 --> 00:31:36.160
along this flat line.

00:31:36.160 --> 00:31:37.750
Very simple, right?

00:31:37.750 --> 00:31:41.000
I like to start with a
really a simple case.

00:31:41.000 --> 00:31:53.280
So what if sigma_1 also is
not 0, but sigma_1 equal

00:31:53.280 --> 00:31:54.830
to sigma_2.

00:31:54.830 --> 00:32:00.714
And further, I impose-- impose--
the correlation to be 0, OK?

00:32:00.714 --> 00:32:01.880
What is this line look like?

00:32:01.880 --> 00:32:04.980
So I have sigma_2
equal to sigma_1.

00:32:09.140 --> 00:32:12.950
And R_1 is still equal
to R_2, so R_P is still

00:32:12.950 --> 00:32:15.750
equal to R_1 or R_2, right?

